Yes — this is the existing error flow we should keep.

Your `ErrorController` already distinguishes:

* `/error/technical`
* `/error/no-sales-point`

and sends these model attributes to `views/ui-error`:

```java
pageTitle
iconPath
title
message
strongMessage
```

The main update is to stop hardcoding French in the controller and resolve the text from `messages.properties`, `messages_fr.properties`, or `messages_nl.properties`.

## Updated controller

```java
package com.bnpp.pf.arthur.core.exception;

import java.util.Locale;

import org.springframework.context.MessageSource;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.servlet.ModelAndView;

@Controller
public class ErrorController {

    private static final String ERROR_VIEW = "views/ui-error";

    private final MessageSource messageSource;

    public ErrorController(MessageSource messageSource) {
        this.messageSource = messageSource;
    }

    @GetMapping("/error/technical")
    public ModelAndView technicalError(Locale locale) {
        return buildErrorView(
                locale,
                "error.technical.pageTitle",
                "/images/icons/tools.svg",
                "error.technical.title",
                "error.technical.message",
                "error.technical.strongMessage"
        );
    }

    @GetMapping("/error/no-sales-point")
    public ModelAndView noSalesPoint(Locale locale) {
        return buildErrorView(
                locale,
                "error.noSalesPoint.pageTitle",
                "/images/icons/warning.svg",
                "error.noSalesPoint.title",
                "error.noSalesPoint.message",
                "error.noSalesPoint.strongMessage"
        );
    }

    private ModelAndView buildErrorView(
            Locale locale,
            String pageTitleKey,
            String iconPath,
            String titleKey,
            String messageKey,
            String strongMessageKey
    ) {
        ModelAndView modelAndView = new ModelAndView(ERROR_VIEW);

        modelAndView.addObject(
                "pageTitle",
                messageSource.getMessage(pageTitleKey, null, locale)
        );
        modelAndView.addObject("iconPath", iconPath);
        modelAndView.addObject(
                "title",
                messageSource.getMessage(titleKey, null, locale)
        );
        modelAndView.addObject(
                "message",
                messageSource.getMessage(messageKey, null, locale)
        );
        modelAndView.addObject(
                "strongMessage",
                messageSource.getMessage(strongMessageKey, null, locale)
        );

        return modelAndView;
    }
}
```

This avoids duplicating the same `ModelAndView` setup in both methods.

