## Keep the template model-based

Because the controller already resolves the translation, your HTML should continue using `${...}`, not `#{...}`:

```html
<title th:text="${pageTitle}">Erreur</title>

<img class="failure-icon"
     th:src="@{${iconPath}}"
     alt="">

<h1 th:text="${title}">
    Oups, un problème technique est survenu.
</h1>

<p class="message"
   th:text="${message}">
    Nous n’avons pas pu charger les données nécessaires.
</p>

<p class="strong-message"
   th:if="${strongMessage != null and !#strings.isEmpty(strongMessage)}"
   th:text="${strongMessage}">
    Réessayez dans quelques minutes.
</p>
```

Use `th:text` for the title unless you intentionally store HTML such as `<br>` in the translation. This keeps the existing controller → shared error template design and adds FR/NL cleanly.
